WEBVTT

00:02.070 --> 00:03.204
Previously on "Chance"...

00:03.237 --> 00:06.040
Chance:
Nic thanked Pepper?

00:06.074 --> 00:08.008
Christina:
Right after she broke her nose.

00:08.042 --> 00:10.478
D: My father hired new PIs
to track me.

00:10.511 --> 00:12.180
It'll just be for
a couple of days.

00:12.213 --> 00:13.814
Why don't you
just talk to him,

00:13.847 --> 00:15.183
just get everything
out on the table,

00:15.216 --> 00:17.485
even if it's only
to establish terms?

00:17.518 --> 00:19.653
My son -- the last time
I saw him,

00:19.687 --> 00:21.355
he was just a little boy.

00:21.389 --> 00:23.757
-What happened?
-Well, gay is what happened.

00:23.791 --> 00:25.726
Lambert:
Winter's people reached out.

00:25.759 --> 00:28.596
I'm telling you, as a friend,
you need to back off.

00:28.629 --> 00:30.331
He wants to torment you,

00:30.364 --> 00:32.066
and you can't let him
get away with it.

00:32.100 --> 00:33.434
We can't.

00:33.467 --> 00:36.036
Hynes: Winter filed
another complaint.

00:36.070 --> 00:37.438
I've lost my job.

00:37.471 --> 00:39.773
Chance: Mr. Winter has
suffered a trauma.

00:39.807 --> 00:41.775
It's raised issues for him
that he wants to work through

00:41.809 --> 00:43.211
with therapy.

00:43.244 --> 00:45.346
Does he want that,
or do you want it?

00:45.379 --> 00:48.082
He says he has to trust
the process, trust you,

00:48.116 --> 00:50.518
but I don't have to,
and I don't.

00:50.551 --> 00:53.053
Winter:
I hurt people.

00:53.087 --> 00:55.523
I hurt them so bad...

00:55.556 --> 00:57.791
that they died.
[ Breathes shakily ]

01:01.662 --> 01:10.471
**

01:10.504 --> 01:19.380
**

01:19.413 --> 01:28.222
**

01:28.256 --> 01:37.097
**

01:37.131 --> 01:45.973
**

01:48.108 --> 01:51.445
Winter: I felt helpless.

01:51.479 --> 01:53.814
Then I found a way not to be.

01:55.983 --> 01:57.585
She woke back up...

01:57.618 --> 01:59.753
at one point.

01:59.787 --> 02:00.921
Regained consciousness.

02:00.954 --> 02:04.325
Mommy! Mommy!

02:04.358 --> 02:07.928
It's funny, she was, uh, pretty
lucid talking about --

02:07.961 --> 02:09.997
well, not funny,

02:10.030 --> 02:14.668
but it's curious, the kinds
of things people will say.

02:17.037 --> 02:19.440
She said that
she was worried about

02:19.473 --> 02:21.609
a driver's test
she had the next morning

02:21.642 --> 02:24.478
and asked me if I was there
to help her study.

02:24.512 --> 02:26.013
To tutor her.

02:26.046 --> 02:27.047
[ Gasps ]

02:31.319 --> 02:34.622
Her name was Catherine.

02:34.655 --> 02:37.157
And she made me
feel better.

02:41.895 --> 02:43.497
That was the first one?

02:45.233 --> 02:47.668
First one you --
you hurt?

02:47.701 --> 02:49.270
You killed?

02:51.004 --> 02:53.374
[ Fire crackling ]

02:56.877 --> 02:58.946
That was your
coping mechanism.

03:00.514 --> 03:02.182
Yes.

03:02.216 --> 03:04.585
But it didn't last.

03:06.287 --> 03:07.555
No.

03:10.424 --> 03:12.993
Once you know how,
you want to feel better again.

03:13.026 --> 03:19.600
**

03:19.633 --> 03:21.134
How many?

03:22.803 --> 03:24.171
How many have there been?

03:24.204 --> 03:29.410
**

03:29.443 --> 03:34.682
**

03:34.715 --> 03:36.784
How do you choose them?

03:36.817 --> 03:38.286
Your victims?

03:38.319 --> 03:40.421
Sins choose us...

03:42.456 --> 03:45.959
...according to
our weaknesses.

03:47.961 --> 03:50.598
But there are people

03:50.631 --> 03:55.436
who shine
with vulnerability,

03:55.469 --> 03:57.805
whether they know it
or not.

03:57.838 --> 03:59.873
Their faces say,

03:59.907 --> 04:02.310
"I am afraid of you."

04:02.343 --> 04:06.146
Their faces tell you what
they expect you to do to them.

04:06.179 --> 04:08.582
They expect to be hurt.

04:08.616 --> 04:10.618
They invite it,

04:10.651 --> 04:14.121
because they expect it.

04:14.154 --> 04:16.824
And if I chose anything,

04:16.857 --> 04:21.795
it was because their weakness
spoke to mine.

04:25.132 --> 04:26.467
Were they all mothers?

04:26.500 --> 04:28.168
[ Breathes shakily ]

04:28.201 --> 04:31.672
A child shines
with vulnerability.

04:33.641 --> 04:36.610
A child who's been hurt
expects to be hurt again.

04:38.346 --> 04:40.280
Does that mean
they deserve it?

04:40.314 --> 04:44.618
Or do they deserve
to be protected?

04:44.652 --> 04:47.755
Cared for? Loved?

04:47.788 --> 04:52.360
**

04:52.393 --> 04:54.261
Who told you this,

04:54.294 --> 04:56.997
about sin and weakness?

04:57.030 --> 04:59.767
Who said that to you?

04:59.800 --> 05:01.935
A very damaged woman

05:01.969 --> 05:05.305
who was carrying her own
terrible psychic pain

05:05.339 --> 05:08.842
she tried to give to you --
pass on to you.

05:08.876 --> 05:10.978
Before
she tried to destroy you.

05:12.380 --> 05:14.014
[ Breathes shakily ]

05:14.047 --> 05:15.883
I'm not dead.

05:15.916 --> 05:18.519
I'm lost,
but I'm not dead.

05:18.552 --> 05:20.320
I'm not dead!

05:20.354 --> 05:28.662
**

05:32.032 --> 05:40.574
**

05:40.608 --> 05:49.149
**

05:49.182 --> 05:50.718
D: Hm.

05:50.751 --> 05:53.153
Old school.

05:53.186 --> 05:54.688
But effective.

05:54.722 --> 05:59.727
**

05:59.760 --> 06:04.765
**

06:04.798 --> 06:06.534
How's this?

06:06.567 --> 06:13.541
**

06:13.574 --> 06:20.514
**

06:20.548 --> 06:22.182
How about now?

06:22.215 --> 06:25.252
**

06:25.285 --> 06:28.756
Fear stops when you kill
the thing you're afraid of.

06:30.624 --> 06:32.593
Or it kills you.

06:32.626 --> 06:41.134
**

06:41.168 --> 06:49.710
**

06:49.743 --> 06:51.912
How many?

06:51.945 --> 06:55.382
He talked about how he kills
them and how he tracked them.

06:55.415 --> 06:56.650
He implied it was many,

06:56.684 --> 06:58.719
but he never actually
said a number.

06:58.752 --> 07:01.455
He did name one, though --
Catherine.

07:01.489 --> 07:03.491
I-I -- I had him.

07:03.524 --> 07:04.925
He was right there with me.

07:04.958 --> 07:06.927
Let's just go for a drive.

07:06.960 --> 07:08.596
Maybe we just
go for a drive.

07:08.629 --> 07:11.732
Yeah. I'll drive you
wherever you want to go.

07:11.765 --> 07:13.266
I don't feel right.

07:13.300 --> 07:15.936
Listen, I think you're
being very brave, Ryan.

07:15.969 --> 07:19.473
You've had to carry this
whole thing alone for so long.

07:19.507 --> 07:21.008
Give me a second.

07:21.041 --> 07:22.409
You know what I think
we should do right now?

07:22.442 --> 07:24.512
I'd like to bring you
to the hospital.

07:24.545 --> 07:26.313
Get you admitted.

07:26.346 --> 07:29.950
You got further than I ever did,
than -- than anyone could.

07:29.983 --> 07:31.418
But then
to fucking lose him...

07:31.451 --> 07:34.121
[ Beep ]
-Kitchen door open.

07:34.154 --> 07:37.357
Oh, no. No, no, no.

07:37.390 --> 07:38.659
What?

07:38.692 --> 07:39.960
She's here.

07:39.993 --> 07:41.962
Ryan,
are you all right?

07:41.995 --> 07:44.464
I'm sorry, I --
What's going on here?

07:44.498 --> 07:46.800
This -- This doesn't
change anything, all right?

07:46.834 --> 07:48.636
I heard you.
I want to help you.

07:48.669 --> 07:50.538
Help him? He's a wreck
because of you.

07:50.571 --> 07:52.840
You can't go back on this now.
You know that.

07:52.873 --> 07:54.642
The only way out of this
is through.

07:54.675 --> 07:55.976
Please come with me now.

07:56.009 --> 07:57.144
Please?
-Come with you?

07:57.177 --> 07:59.146
Ryan, please!

07:59.179 --> 08:00.981
Chance: I don't know if
he actually wanted to stop.

08:01.014 --> 08:02.850
You know what people do
that don't want to stop?

08:02.883 --> 08:04.985
They keep fucking going.

08:05.018 --> 08:06.854
-He wants you to leave.
-He didn't say that.

08:06.887 --> 08:08.388
He doesn't need to.

08:08.421 --> 08:09.389
What?

08:09.422 --> 08:11.792
Maybe I should call 911.

08:11.825 --> 08:15.729
Go ahead.
Let's get the police here.

08:15.763 --> 08:17.665
You're awfully confident.

08:17.698 --> 08:19.366
Wonder why that is.

08:22.235 --> 08:23.871
You're ready?

08:23.904 --> 08:25.372
Let's call them.

08:26.574 --> 08:28.275
[ Sighs ]

08:31.244 --> 08:33.513
I didn't get him to
turn himself in,

08:33.547 --> 08:34.882
I didn't get him
to admit anything

08:34.915 --> 08:36.817
that I could legally
take to the police.

08:36.850 --> 08:38.819
I should've --

08:38.852 --> 08:40.588
My head was just fill--
I wanted to...

08:40.621 --> 08:42.422
Hynes: What?
Get yourself arrested?

08:42.455 --> 08:46.326
Fuck that. You played it
the way you could.

08:46.359 --> 08:48.929
And you -- you didn't blow it.
You got us a name -- Catherine.

08:48.962 --> 08:51.431
I've never heard of
any unsolved Catherines.

08:51.464 --> 08:53.200
Maybe they never
found her body.

08:53.233 --> 08:56.069
Or maybe she's one of the bodies
out in the Headlands, even.

08:56.103 --> 08:58.772
I'm gonna look into that.

08:58.806 --> 09:02.209
-Look into it how?
-Well, I mean, I'm --

09:02.242 --> 09:04.344
I'm gonna look into having
someone look into it for me.

09:04.377 --> 09:07.547
I've got this friend
Frank at the D.A.'s office

09:07.581 --> 09:09.683
who doesn't
completely hate me yet --

09:09.717 --> 09:11.885
I c-- I can ask him.

09:13.420 --> 09:15.589
Oh, and speaking of
looking into things,

09:15.623 --> 09:17.625
that fucking Lyndsay,

09:17.658 --> 09:20.127
I looked into her way back when,
and nothing.

09:20.160 --> 09:21.929
Where is she from?

09:21.962 --> 09:24.397
Uh, Connecticut or some shit.
Why?

09:24.431 --> 09:27.400
I don't know. Just grasping
at straws, I guess.

09:29.169 --> 09:31.204
Maybe Winter doesn't
have any involvement

09:31.238 --> 09:33.073
with Stevie Benjamin's
death.

09:33.106 --> 09:36.209
Oh, well, this is --
Christ.

09:36.243 --> 09:38.245
Maybe he just had a
morbid fascination with it,

09:38.278 --> 09:41.081
from growing up close by.

09:41.114 --> 09:42.883
Maybe the rock that
D found in his house

09:42.916 --> 09:44.417
doesn't have the significance
we thought it did.

09:44.451 --> 09:46.319
Maybe since we're dreaming,
I'd like a pony.

09:46.353 --> 09:47.921
I know. I-I agree.

09:47.955 --> 09:49.790
I'm just saying, if we're not
dreaming, if we are right,

09:49.823 --> 09:53.226
then we still don't actually
know who that DNA belongs to.

09:53.260 --> 09:55.095
No, we don't, do we?

09:56.596 --> 10:01.401
So,
Winter admitted that his...

10:01.434 --> 10:04.905
coping mechanism
is killing.

10:04.938 --> 10:07.975
And he also admitted that
it's not working anymore.

10:08.008 --> 10:11.244
I don't even want to think about
how he came to that conclusion.

10:11.278 --> 10:13.413
I've got enough on
my conscience as it is.

10:13.446 --> 10:16.684
Right now, my focus has
to be to get him back.

10:18.218 --> 10:19.853
You know, when I was
sitting opposite him,

10:19.887 --> 10:22.690
he was rambling on about
dealing out death...

10:24.191 --> 10:26.259
...I thought about dealing it
right back at him.

10:26.293 --> 10:29.096
More than once.

10:29.129 --> 10:32.766
I don't know how you do it,
all those years.

10:32.800 --> 10:36.003
Sitting opposite killers,
encouraging them,

10:36.036 --> 10:37.938
getting them to
elaborate without --

10:37.971 --> 10:40.173
Stabbing them
in the fucking eye?

10:40.207 --> 10:44.644
**

10:44.678 --> 10:45.846
Let me tell you something.

10:45.879 --> 10:47.347
You know how many times

10:47.380 --> 10:50.017
I pulled out my piece
in the line of duty?

10:50.050 --> 10:53.053
7 -- 26 years.

10:53.086 --> 10:54.621
You know how many times
I've shot it?

10:54.654 --> 10:55.823
Once.

10:55.856 --> 10:58.525
You know how many people
I've killed?

10:58.558 --> 11:01.194
None.

11:01.228 --> 11:03.130
If you're not acting
in self-defense,

11:03.163 --> 11:05.298
or the active defense
of someone else,

11:05.332 --> 11:08.135
then you're
a fucking murderer.

11:08.168 --> 11:09.803
Ryan Winter is a murderer.

11:09.837 --> 11:13.673
And that's who
he wants to be.

11:13.707 --> 11:16.176
I'm not gonna be like him.

11:16.209 --> 11:19.012
We have a deal.

11:19.046 --> 11:21.982
Ryan Winter in front
of the bar of justice,

11:22.015 --> 11:24.484
to bare all before
the whole world.

11:24.517 --> 11:27.520
I'm gonna do this
the right way.

11:27.554 --> 11:29.857
Not Ryan Winter's way.

11:29.890 --> 11:34.561
**

11:34.594 --> 11:36.764
And your super-sized friend?

11:39.632 --> 11:44.037
I'm sure he's gonna be
asking the same question.

11:44.071 --> 11:46.239
So, you're gonna have
to tell him that we --

11:46.273 --> 11:48.675
we have a deal.

11:48.708 --> 11:53.246
**

11:59.719 --> 12:01.922
Stone:
His parole officer called me,
told me he'd been working

12:01.955 --> 12:05.725
in a 24-hour garage in Daly City
for about the last month.

12:05.759 --> 12:08.695
Called over and talked
to the manager.
And?

12:08.728 --> 12:11.398
And Pardo's not
the most popular guy there.

12:11.431 --> 12:13.533
So when some big bald guy
showed up recently

12:13.566 --> 12:16.603
and gave him a beatdown,
nobody was that surprised.

12:16.636 --> 12:18.271
Or sad.

12:18.305 --> 12:20.407
Broke a bunch of bones,
put him in the hospital.

12:20.440 --> 12:21.975
When he got out,

12:22.009 --> 12:23.576
went to live with his sister
in Castro Valley.

12:26.146 --> 12:28.248
So, uh, what's the deal?

12:28.281 --> 12:30.383
Who's this Pardo guy to you?

12:30.417 --> 12:35.889
**

12:35.923 --> 12:37.891
[ Men grunting ]

12:37.925 --> 12:39.927
[ Sticks clacking ]

12:43.596 --> 12:45.465
D: Hinto.

12:47.767 --> 12:49.436
Mass attack.

12:51.138 --> 12:52.539
I need six guys.

12:55.108 --> 12:57.044
I want you to come at me, hard.

12:58.611 --> 13:00.313
I want you to really
try to hurt me.

13:00.347 --> 13:03.283
And I'm gonna really
try to hurt you.

13:06.286 --> 13:08.521
Ready?

13:08.555 --> 13:12.125
* I can see for miles
-I'm taking this dog.

13:12.159 --> 13:14.261
-No! Please. He's mine!
-You can't take care of it, man.

13:14.294 --> 13:15.929
You know that.
This is an animal abuse.

13:15.963 --> 13:17.497
-Hey, come on, man.
-That's his dog.

13:17.530 --> 13:19.299
Woman: Yeah, well,
he can't help himself.

13:19.332 --> 13:21.034
How's he gonna help the dog?
-No, please!

13:21.068 --> 13:23.503
Put your phones away.
It deserves to be protected.

13:23.536 --> 13:25.472
It deserves a home!
-Hey! You're hurting him!

13:25.505 --> 13:28.942
-Hey, watch it.
-No!

13:28.976 --> 13:31.044
[ Crying ]

13:31.078 --> 13:33.947
Man: Get their plates.

13:33.981 --> 13:35.949
Ohh!

13:35.983 --> 13:39.619
[ Crying continues ]

13:39.652 --> 13:44.324
Woman #2: Who does that?

13:44.357 --> 13:47.027
[ Indistinct conversations ]

13:47.060 --> 13:57.037
* Angel just above the grid

13:57.070 --> 14:03.176
**

14:03.210 --> 14:11.084
* Open, smiling, reach out

14:11.118 --> 14:19.759
**

14:20.894 --> 14:22.429
[ Door closes ]

14:26.633 --> 14:29.869
[ Grunts ]

14:31.871 --> 14:33.173
Hey.

14:33.206 --> 14:36.076
Dad's not here.

14:36.109 --> 14:37.177
I know.

14:37.210 --> 14:38.711
Futon's all yours again.

14:38.745 --> 14:40.680
[ Zippers zipping ]

14:40.713 --> 14:42.515
-Hey, you okay?
-Yep.

14:42.549 --> 14:44.884
-You get in a fight?
-Nope.

14:46.653 --> 14:48.288
What are you working on?

14:51.791 --> 14:53.693
This morning,
I saw this rich couple

14:53.726 --> 14:55.595
steal
a homeless guy's dog.

14:55.628 --> 14:57.230
At least they looked
like they were rich.

14:57.264 --> 14:59.032
So mean and shitty.

14:59.066 --> 15:01.969
They just yanked it right out
of his arms and drove away.

15:02.002 --> 15:04.204
We all just stood
there watching.

15:04.237 --> 15:06.139
Or even worse,
filming it.

15:06.173 --> 15:07.574
How fucked up is that?

15:07.607 --> 15:09.476
-Pretty fucked up.
-Yeah.

15:09.509 --> 15:12.245
So, anyway, I'm trying
to find them

15:12.279 --> 15:14.547
through the gross magic
of social media.

15:14.581 --> 15:16.950
[ Keyboard clacking ]

15:16.984 --> 15:19.286
The rich hipster couple.
-To do what?

15:19.319 --> 15:21.321
I don't know.
Talk to them.

15:21.354 --> 15:23.090
Say if they let me
take the dog back,

15:23.123 --> 15:24.992
I'll keep an eye on it
if they're worried,

15:25.025 --> 15:27.160
make sure it gets
its shots and whatever.

15:27.194 --> 15:31.131
That way, everyone
can get what they want.

15:31.164 --> 15:34.301
These rich people
you're talking about --

15:34.334 --> 15:36.169
they have what they want.

15:36.203 --> 15:38.271
They don't care about you.

15:39.806 --> 15:42.142
Before you even
open your mouth,

15:42.175 --> 15:44.044
you'll be wasting their time.

15:45.678 --> 15:47.347
You can plan shit
out in your head.

15:48.681 --> 15:50.683
Everything you want
to do and say --

15:50.717 --> 15:53.920
everything you think
the other guy might do or say.

15:53.953 --> 15:55.989
But when you get to it,

15:56.023 --> 15:58.658
nothing is like you planned.

15:58.691 --> 16:00.160
Ever.

16:00.193 --> 16:02.695
Okay.

16:02.729 --> 16:05.632
If I left anything here that
you find, just throw it away.

16:05.665 --> 16:09.102
**

16:09.136 --> 16:12.439
[ Door opens, closes ]

16:12.472 --> 16:16.676
[ Indistinct conversations ]

16:16.709 --> 16:19.046
Hey, I got it. I got it.
Thanks.

16:19.079 --> 16:20.880
Knock, knock.

16:20.913 --> 16:22.515
-Kev.
-Frank.

16:22.549 --> 16:23.883
My man.

16:23.916 --> 16:25.552
That thing you're
working on pan out?

16:25.585 --> 16:27.320
What's up?
-Yeah. No.

16:27.354 --> 16:29.822
We had a little setback there,
but we're still on track.

16:29.856 --> 16:32.559
Uh-huh.
But, in the meantime,
I could use a favor.

16:32.592 --> 16:33.993
Well, a couple of them,
actually.

16:34.027 --> 16:36.196
[ Chuckles ]
Jesus wept.

16:36.229 --> 16:39.399
Katherine Atkins.
-Mm. Mother of two.

16:39.432 --> 16:42.902
And the DOJ website
reported her missing in 2005

16:42.935 --> 16:44.504
in, uh,
Alameda County.

16:44.537 --> 16:47.840
So I called Alameda PD
and got the run-around.

16:47.874 --> 16:50.377
And long story short,
they found a body,

16:50.410 --> 16:52.179
but they won't
tell me shit.

16:52.212 --> 16:53.846
Well, like, what do
you want to know?

16:53.880 --> 16:56.015
Well, for starters,
I'd like to know how she died.

16:56.049 --> 17:00.353
And also, whether there were,
uh, rocks in her throat.

17:02.589 --> 17:06.759
Okay. I'm not even --
Yeah, I can make a call.
Okay.

17:06.793 --> 17:08.528
What else?

17:08.561 --> 17:10.163
You, uh, know somebody

17:10.197 --> 17:11.564
in the State's
Attorney's office

17:11.598 --> 17:13.700
in Bridgeport, right?

17:13.733 --> 17:15.034
In Bridgeport?

17:15.068 --> 17:16.503
You're talking
Bridgeport, Connecticut?

17:16.536 --> 17:18.037
-Yes.
-Jesus Christ, buddy.

17:18.071 --> 17:21.241
You are -- You are
all over the map today.

17:21.274 --> 17:23.042
Yes, I do. Why?

17:23.076 --> 17:25.345
Great. Can you ask them
to run that sheet?

17:25.378 --> 17:27.680
I'm looking for any
expunged criminal records.

17:27.714 --> 17:29.849
I mean, I --
Look, I ran her a few years ago,

17:29.882 --> 17:32.585
but I only did it
in California, so...

17:32.619 --> 17:34.787
Who's Lyndsay Hamilton?

17:34.821 --> 17:37.424
Well, she's, uh,
Winter's assistant.

17:37.457 --> 17:38.858
-Wint-- Come on.
-Yeah, I know.

17:38.891 --> 17:40.793
-Kevin, why?
-I know, but listen to me.

17:40.827 --> 17:42.962
I'm just thinking maybe Winter
had some help along the way.

17:42.995 --> 17:44.964
So let's just leave it at that.
-No, but that's just it.

17:44.997 --> 17:49.102
Help with what?
And...based on what?

17:52.839 --> 17:54.474
Kevin,
not for nothing,

17:54.507 --> 17:58.711
but being your friend is like
having a goddamn colonoscopy.

17:58.745 --> 18:00.747
Please, Frank?

18:00.780 --> 18:03.250
I need your help.
Please.

18:07.320 --> 18:09.622
Okay.

18:09.656 --> 18:11.057
Thank you.

18:11.090 --> 18:12.292
Appreciate it.

18:12.325 --> 18:13.760
-Now leave me alone?
-Yes.

18:13.793 --> 18:16.663
-Please?
-For today, I will.

18:16.696 --> 18:18.998
Thanks again, Frank.

18:20.167 --> 18:22.635
[ Line ringing ]

18:22.669 --> 18:24.837
Hi. This is Ryan.
Leave a message.

18:24.871 --> 18:26.273
[ Beep ]

18:26.306 --> 18:29.476
Ryan, it's Eldon Chance
here again.

18:29.509 --> 18:31.511
Please call me.

18:31.544 --> 18:33.680
Please reach out, okay?

18:33.713 --> 18:35.782
I-I-I need to know
you're all right.

18:35.815 --> 18:39.619
I'm here to help you.
I want to help you.

18:39.652 --> 18:42.121
Okay.

18:42.155 --> 18:48.661
**

18:48.695 --> 18:51.498
[ Cellphone rings ]

18:53.866 --> 18:54.967
Ryan?

18:55.001 --> 18:58.037
Lyndsay:
Stop calling him!

18:58.070 --> 19:02.442
Lyndsay, Mr. Winter is
in a fragile state right now.

19:02.475 --> 19:04.344
He needs constant
medical supervision.

19:04.377 --> 19:07.614
It's possible he might hurt
himself or someone else.

19:07.647 --> 19:10.450
I will lodge a formal complaint
with the state medical board.

19:10.483 --> 19:11.951
I get it.
You care about him.

19:11.984 --> 19:14.053
So do I.
We're on the same side here.

19:14.086 --> 19:16.556
you will lose your license,
face charges.

19:16.589 --> 19:17.890
Should I keep going?

19:17.924 --> 19:20.227
Listen, if anything
happens to him,

19:20.260 --> 19:21.828
you could be
held responsible.

19:21.861 --> 19:24.864
I am trying my best
to be civil, Dr. Chance.

19:24.897 --> 19:29.035
You don't want to see
what happens when I stop.

19:29.068 --> 19:32.339
Or maybe I do, Lyndsay.

19:32.372 --> 19:34.741
Maybe that way, I'll find out
what it is you're hiding.

19:34.774 --> 19:39.912
**

19:43.416 --> 19:45.952
[ Woman speaking indistinctly
on PA ]

19:49.856 --> 19:50.957
-Hey.
-Hey.

19:56.062 --> 19:59.766
[ Sighs ]

19:59.799 --> 20:02.101
So, full disclosure?

20:02.134 --> 20:05.605
That could mean almost anything,
but sure.

20:07.307 --> 20:08.708
I found Wade Pardo.

20:08.741 --> 20:11.444
Okay?

20:11.478 --> 20:13.246
I know you said you thought
he wouldn't come back here,

20:13.280 --> 20:15.348
but still.

20:15.382 --> 20:18.718
I asked a cop friend of mine
to try and track him down.

20:18.751 --> 20:20.587
In case.

20:22.422 --> 20:23.823
And what'd you find out?

20:26.293 --> 20:28.761
He was working in Daly City,
at a garage,

20:28.795 --> 20:31.431
and then somebody showed up
and threw him a beatdown.

20:31.464 --> 20:32.965
Broke a lot of bones.

20:32.999 --> 20:35.935
Not too long after
his run-in with you.

20:35.968 --> 20:38.905
Same thing happened to
Matty Willis a couple weeks ago.

20:40.473 --> 20:41.774
He's the guy who broke into

20:41.808 --> 20:43.576
Clara Santiago's apartment
and raped her.

20:43.610 --> 20:45.144
I think that the charge
was dropped

20:45.177 --> 20:48.114
on an illegal search issue.

20:48.147 --> 20:49.582
But Clara came
and told me that --

20:49.616 --> 20:52.452
that Matty'd been robbed,
he'd been stabbed.

20:52.485 --> 20:55.888
He survived, but one of the
nerves in his arm was severed.

20:55.922 --> 20:58.257
Really?
I didn't hear about that.

20:58.291 --> 21:01.494
Well, honestly,
if we followed up

21:01.528 --> 21:03.730
on every person
who put a patient in here,

21:03.763 --> 21:05.332
I think we'd find
the percentage of them

21:05.365 --> 21:07.066
volunteering in soup kitchens

21:07.099 --> 21:09.936
and helping old ladies across
the street would be pretty low.

21:11.203 --> 21:14.641
Those who live by the sword,
die by the sword, I guess.

21:14.674 --> 21:16.843
Or get maimed by the sword.

21:16.876 --> 21:19.178
And our job is to deal
with the fallout.

21:19.211 --> 21:22.715
And we've got enough fallout
to last the rest of our lives.

21:24.684 --> 21:27.687
Speaking of which...
[ Exhales shakily ]

21:27.720 --> 21:30.189
Didn't you come in
to get coffee?

21:31.891 --> 21:34.427
Yeah, I did.

21:34.461 --> 21:35.962
Obviously I need it.

21:35.995 --> 21:38.898
[ Chuckles ]

21:40.232 --> 21:43.836
[ Keyboard clacking ]

21:45.738 --> 21:48.140
**

21:48.174 --> 21:50.777
-Come on.
-How's he gonna help the dog?

21:50.810 --> 21:52.445
Put your phones away.
-What gives you the right?

21:52.479 --> 21:56.115
[ Dog barks ]
-You're hurting him!

21:56.148 --> 21:59.486
[ Indistinct chatter ]

21:59.519 --> 22:00.987
Man: Crazy messed up.
Get the plates.

22:01.020 --> 22:03.823
Woman: Ohh.

22:03.856 --> 22:06.659
[ Keyboard clacking ]

22:06.693 --> 22:08.194
Woman: What the hell?

22:08.227 --> 22:09.462
Man: No, no!

22:09.496 --> 22:11.163
Go, go, go!

22:11.197 --> 22:12.565
Stop it!

22:12.599 --> 22:14.667
Man #2: Crazy messed up.
Get the plates.

22:14.701 --> 22:24.010
**

22:24.043 --> 22:33.352
**

22:33.386 --> 22:42.662
**

22:42.695 --> 22:52.004
**

22:52.038 --> 23:01.380
**

23:03.883 --> 23:05.952
Oh, that's closed now.

23:05.985 --> 23:08.120
It was up on 18th.

23:08.154 --> 23:10.890
It's the only place
I could go.

23:10.923 --> 23:13.259
Come on, there weren't
any other gay bars

23:13.292 --> 23:15.061
in the Castro in the '70s?

23:15.094 --> 23:18.064
The only place
a black man could go.
Ah.

23:18.097 --> 23:20.533
Besides Oakland.

23:20.567 --> 23:23.770
Ah.
So what happened?

23:26.105 --> 23:29.241
I became...
[Sighs]

23:29.275 --> 23:31.578
incautious.

23:31.611 --> 23:33.045
If once a week was fine,

23:33.079 --> 23:35.648
four times a week
was that much better.

23:35.682 --> 23:39.218
Mm-hmm.
I told myself,
before I told Olivia,

23:39.251 --> 23:41.888
I was trying to find
what exactly it was

23:41.921 --> 23:43.923
that I was telling her.

23:43.956 --> 23:47.293
And while I was finding out,
she found me out.

23:47.326 --> 23:48.995
Oh.

23:49.028 --> 23:53.265
Took Alvin to her mother's
and followed me to the Pendulum.

23:53.299 --> 23:55.735
Oh, shit.

23:55.768 --> 23:58.738
It was a betrayal,
no question.

23:58.771 --> 24:01.307
Made worse by having
been discovered,

24:01.340 --> 24:03.175
rather than confessed.

24:05.311 --> 24:08.147
So, you -- you never thought
about just giving it up?

24:08.180 --> 24:10.449
I mean, pretending
that it never happened

24:10.483 --> 24:12.685
and saying
it was a mistake?

24:12.719 --> 24:16.288
You can't close your eyes
once they've been opened.

24:16.322 --> 24:19.391
[ Groans ]

24:20.793 --> 24:23.996
No, you can't.

24:24.030 --> 24:27.333
You know, you may not be
a married man with a child,

24:27.366 --> 24:29.168
but still.

24:29.201 --> 24:31.103
People are going to
look at you differently,

24:31.137 --> 24:32.839
and that's fine.

24:32.872 --> 24:36.208
If you are strong
in yourself.

24:36.242 --> 24:39.178
And, Kevin,
I see that you are.

24:39.211 --> 24:41.380
You are strong.

24:41.413 --> 24:44.350
You are ready.

24:44.383 --> 24:46.986
You are a treasure
in a jar of clay.

24:49.055 --> 24:50.723
-Yeah?
-[ Chuckles ]

24:50.757 --> 24:52.458
Yes, indeed.

24:52.491 --> 24:56.395
Pressed on all sides,
but not crushed.

24:56.428 --> 24:59.899
Perplexed,
but not in despair.

24:59.932 --> 25:03.803
Persecuted,
but never forsaken.

25:03.836 --> 25:07.406
Struck down,
but never destroyed.

25:07.439 --> 25:09.041
Now...

25:09.075 --> 25:10.743
have another cup of tea.

25:14.380 --> 25:16.248
Yeah.

25:16.282 --> 25:17.850
Ahh.

25:17.884 --> 25:19.185
Mm-hmm.

25:20.119 --> 25:21.420
Woman:
Yeah, you need to stretch more.

25:21.453 --> 25:23.189
I don't know why guys
don't stretch.

25:23.222 --> 25:25.391
[ Speaking indistinctly ]

25:25.424 --> 25:35.034
**

25:35.067 --> 25:44.611
**

25:44.644 --> 25:54.253
**

25:54.286 --> 26:03.896
**

26:03.930 --> 26:13.539
**

26:13.572 --> 26:23.115
**

26:23.149 --> 26:32.759
**

26:32.792 --> 26:35.261
[ Dog barking ]

26:35.294 --> 26:36.963
**

26:36.996 --> 26:38.497
[ Chuckles lightly ]

26:38.530 --> 26:41.333
[ Gasps, laughs ]

26:41.367 --> 26:44.003
Oh, yeah!

26:44.036 --> 26:45.571
Oh, my God!

26:45.604 --> 26:48.107
Where'd you come from, huh?
Huh? Huh?

26:48.140 --> 26:54.413
[ Laughs ]

26:54.446 --> 26:57.950
Oh, I'm so glad
to have you back.

26:58.851 --> 27:00.987
Chance: So, you're here again?

27:01.020 --> 27:03.823
Safe to come back now?

27:03.856 --> 27:05.224
All good, brother.

27:08.695 --> 27:10.329
Say it.

27:10.362 --> 27:11.664
Your face.

27:11.698 --> 27:13.165
I needed to
work something out.

27:13.199 --> 27:15.434
Something that
didn't feel finished.

27:15.467 --> 27:17.036
So I did.

27:17.069 --> 27:18.771
And it does.

27:18.805 --> 27:22.108
Winter.
You get back with him yet?

27:22.141 --> 27:24.844
No, not yet.
It's not for want of trying.

27:24.877 --> 27:27.346
I drove by his place,
I left a ton of messages.

27:27.379 --> 27:29.515
Why is he
stonewalling now?

27:29.548 --> 27:31.617
Oh, it's Lyndsay who's doing
the stonewalling.

27:31.650 --> 27:33.052
I don't know
what Winter's doing.

27:33.085 --> 27:35.154
Fucking Eva Braun.

27:35.187 --> 27:37.623
I hope Hynes can dig
something up on her.

27:37.656 --> 27:39.391
Yeah, so do I,

27:39.425 --> 27:41.027
but that doesn't help me
right now.

27:41.060 --> 27:44.196
Right now the problem is that
she's denying me access.

27:44.230 --> 27:46.866
Every hour that passes
is an hour lost.

27:46.899 --> 27:48.467
Winter
could change his story,

27:48.500 --> 27:51.370
change his mind,
he can end the game.

27:54.707 --> 27:59.011
Unless...

27:59.045 --> 28:02.514
Unless we can separate
the sheep from the sheepdog.

28:05.351 --> 28:06.819
Awesome.

28:10.757 --> 28:13.826
Woman: There is the instance
where a monk,

28:13.860 --> 28:16.162
having gone into
the wilderness,

28:16.195 --> 28:19.398
sits down under
the shade of a tree,

28:19.431 --> 28:24.503
setting mindfulness
to the fore.

28:24.536 --> 28:26.172
Always mindful,

28:26.205 --> 28:29.175
he breathes in.

28:29.208 --> 28:30.877
Always mindful,

28:30.910 --> 28:33.045
he breathes out.

28:35.214 --> 28:39.685
Always mindful...
[ Cellphone vibrating ]

28:39.718 --> 28:41.187
Yes?

28:41.220 --> 28:43.722
Hynes: Hey, Lyndsay.

28:43.756 --> 28:45.457
Who is this?

28:45.491 --> 28:48.027
Well, you filed the complaint
that got me fired --

28:48.060 --> 28:50.029
seems like you
should know who I am.

28:50.062 --> 28:52.464
You got yourself fired.

28:52.498 --> 28:56.135
Now, it seems you want to get
yourself arrested, as well.

28:56.168 --> 28:58.070
Crazy, right?

28:58.104 --> 28:59.872
What the fuck
am I thinking?

28:59.906 --> 29:02.741
Don't you ever wonder?
-Don't I ever wonder what?

29:02.775 --> 29:04.543
What I'm thinking.

29:04.576 --> 29:06.612
Why I would throw away
a 30-year career

29:06.645 --> 29:10.382
and let my life go
to shit over your boss?

29:10.416 --> 29:13.119
Or what I might know
that you don't?

29:13.152 --> 29:17.156
Come meet me right now and I'll
tell you what you don't know.

29:17.189 --> 29:19.325
I'll even let you
pick the place.

29:19.358 --> 29:22.661
Public place if it
makes you feel safer.

29:22.694 --> 29:24.396
But pick it right now.

29:24.430 --> 29:26.498
Before I change my mind.

29:26.532 --> 29:29.201
Or you'll never get the answers
you've always wanted.

29:32.872 --> 29:34.974
He's in his room.
Mr. Winter.

29:35.007 --> 29:37.743
I have to run out,
but I'll be back soon.

29:37.776 --> 29:40.412
I'm going to end this insanity
once and for all.

29:40.446 --> 29:43.482
Just call me if you need me,
but don't leave.

29:43.515 --> 29:45.952
And don't let anyone in.

29:50.389 --> 29:52.458
Man on TV: Easiest non-cheese
mac and cheese...

29:52.491 --> 29:54.994
[ Pounding on door ]
Christina:
Nic, are you in there?

29:55.027 --> 29:57.363
[ Pounding continues ]
Nicole, open the door!

29:57.396 --> 30:00.132
... packed full of
nutrients, proteins...

30:00.166 --> 30:02.368
[ Pounding continues ]
Nic, open the door!

30:02.401 --> 30:04.670
[ Pounding continues ]

30:04.703 --> 30:05.938
Hey.

30:05.972 --> 30:07.373
Why didn't you
answer your phone?

30:07.406 --> 30:09.041
I-I don't know.
It's charging in the kitchen.

30:09.075 --> 30:10.709
Why? What's wrong?

30:10.742 --> 30:12.511
Don't worry.
It's gonna be fine.

30:12.544 --> 30:15.014
I hired a lawyer and he's gonna
meet us down there, okay?

30:15.047 --> 30:16.548
We will figure this out.
Don't worry.

30:16.582 --> 30:18.384
Mom,
don't worry about what?

30:21.921 --> 30:24.023
M-Mom,
they stole his dog!

30:24.056 --> 30:25.724
I-I just took it back to him.
I never did --

30:25.757 --> 30:27.526
I promise!
Nic, what are you saying?
Stop talking.

30:27.559 --> 30:30.196
Nicole Chance, you're under
arrest for aggravated assault.

30:30.229 --> 30:33.565
Please place your hands
behind your back.

30:33.599 --> 30:35.634
Pepper's parents
are pressing charges.

30:35.667 --> 30:38.304
It's gonna be fine.
I-I promise.

30:38.337 --> 30:40.272
We'll figure this out.

30:43.375 --> 30:46.712
[ Indistinct conversations ]

30:46.745 --> 30:49.348
[ Door opens ]

30:49.381 --> 30:51.183
[ Door closes ]

30:57.523 --> 31:04.263
**

31:04.296 --> 31:07.066
Hynes: Ramona Marquez,
34, one son --

31:07.099 --> 31:08.734
he cut her throat.

31:10.469 --> 31:14.273
Ivy Maitland, 31.

31:14.306 --> 31:15.774
She had a son.

31:15.807 --> 31:17.609
He cut her throat.

31:19.445 --> 31:23.916
And Josefa Pefaur, 30.

31:23.950 --> 31:26.953
Twin girls and a baby
on the way.

31:26.986 --> 31:29.121
Winter met her
in group therapy,

31:29.155 --> 31:31.757
at the Victims
of Violent Crime Unit.

31:31.790 --> 31:32.992
Cut her throat.

31:36.495 --> 31:39.765
Katherine, Travis, Su Yee,

31:39.798 --> 31:44.303
Leigh Ann, Ramona,
Ivy, and Josefa.

31:44.336 --> 31:46.605
That's as many
as I'm sure of.

31:46.638 --> 31:50.109
And I don't believe that
that's all there are.

31:50.142 --> 31:53.645
So...these are things
you think I need to hear?

31:53.679 --> 31:55.481
No.

31:55.514 --> 31:58.350
Those are the things
that everyone needs to hear.

32:01.587 --> 32:03.455
When Winter was 4 years old,

32:03.489 --> 32:07.059
his name was Matthew Debbs.

32:07.093 --> 32:10.329
This is a picture
of his mother, Amy.

32:12.331 --> 32:14.300
When Amy was 33 years old,

32:14.333 --> 32:18.304
she tried to kill herself
by cutting her own throat.

32:18.337 --> 32:19.771
But it didn't work.

32:21.540 --> 32:25.277
So she tried to
kill Matthew instead.

32:25.311 --> 32:26.745
Now, I'm not sure,

32:26.778 --> 32:29.982
but it's probably
why he does what he does.

32:30.016 --> 32:32.584
I mean,
it seems pretty likely.

32:32.618 --> 32:34.753
But still, if I could,

32:34.786 --> 32:37.323
I'd talk to him about it.

32:37.356 --> 32:40.792
I mean, wouldn't you...
like to talk to him about it?

32:40.826 --> 32:43.395
Or...do you not need to?

32:46.065 --> 32:48.234
Do you know everything,
Lyndsay?

32:52.071 --> 32:53.239
I'm done.

32:54.373 --> 32:55.641
Well, I'm not.

32:55.674 --> 32:57.809
When I am, you'll know.

32:59.645 --> 33:02.548
Woman: And how are the factors
for awakening

33:02.581 --> 33:04.983
developed and pursued

33:05.017 --> 33:07.119
so as to bring clear knowing

33:07.153 --> 33:10.556
and release
to their culmination?

33:12.824 --> 33:15.561
A monk develops mindfulness

33:15.594 --> 33:19.031
as a factor for awakening.

33:19.065 --> 33:24.303
Persistence as a factor
for awakening.

33:24.336 --> 33:29.975
Concentration as a factor
for awakening.

33:30.008 --> 33:35.147
Serenity as a factor
for awakening.

33:35.181 --> 33:38.817
Dependent on seclusion.

33:38.850 --> 33:41.587
Dependent on dispassion.

33:41.620 --> 33:44.556
Dependent on closure.

33:44.590 --> 33:48.560
Resulting in surrender.

33:48.594 --> 33:56.502
**

33:56.535 --> 34:04.410
**

34:04.443 --> 34:12.351
**

34:12.384 --> 34:14.820
Lyndsay?

34:18.056 --> 34:19.625
Lyndsay?!

34:19.658 --> 34:21.093
Chance: It's okay, Ryan.

34:22.461 --> 34:24.696
I'm here.

34:24.730 --> 34:26.598
You're here with me.

34:28.400 --> 34:30.402
[ Breathing shakily ]

34:38.944 --> 34:41.147
Um...

34:41.180 --> 34:43.449
Where the fuck is here?

34:45.151 --> 34:47.453
This is a safe place.

34:47.486 --> 34:50.789
I brought you here because
I thought it was best.

34:50.822 --> 34:55.427
A quiet place for us to
finish what you started.

34:55.461 --> 34:56.995
You're not a prisoner.

34:57.028 --> 34:58.797
Ryan, you're not a hostage.

34:58.830 --> 35:00.932
You want to call someone,
you can call Lyndsay

35:00.966 --> 35:02.701
or you could call
the police if you want.

35:07.473 --> 35:09.675
[ Cellphone clatters ]

35:09.708 --> 35:12.811
You can tell them that
you were kidnapped,

35:12.844 --> 35:14.613
brought here
against your will.

35:14.646 --> 35:16.515
It's up to you.

35:19.351 --> 35:21.119
I told you things.

35:21.153 --> 35:22.954
And I know
you're not finished.

35:25.957 --> 35:27.826
No, I can't. I can't.

35:27.859 --> 35:29.428
Yeah, you can.

35:29.461 --> 35:31.597
I'm not going to prison.

35:31.630 --> 35:33.131
I'm not asking you to.

35:37.669 --> 35:39.671
I've seen this before,
Ryan.

35:41.673 --> 35:44.643
I had a patient. A woman.

35:44.676 --> 35:47.513
She went through this, too.

35:47.546 --> 35:49.481
She and I did.
Together.

35:49.515 --> 35:51.717
Who was she?

35:51.750 --> 35:53.719
What was wrong with her?

35:57.323 --> 35:59.491
She hurt people.

35:59.525 --> 36:00.826
Like you did.

36:00.859 --> 36:03.028
Like you do.

36:03.061 --> 36:05.464
She also had
a history of abuse,

36:05.497 --> 36:07.533
going back to when
she was a child.

36:07.566 --> 36:12.170
She was beset by feelings
of guilt and rage, remorse...

36:12.204 --> 36:14.906
Retreating
into dissociation.

36:14.940 --> 36:18.477
She also told me that
she couldn't face prison.

36:18.510 --> 36:21.647
She was too afraid.

36:21.680 --> 36:23.915
But, as afraid as she was...

36:26.184 --> 36:29.488
she trusted me more.

36:29.521 --> 36:32.558
She admitted
what she'd done.

36:32.591 --> 36:34.025
In court.

36:34.059 --> 36:35.994
There was a plea
of diminished capacity,

36:36.027 --> 36:38.029
and I testified
on her behalf.

36:38.063 --> 36:39.898
She was committed to
a psychiatric hospital.

36:39.931 --> 36:41.567
Not a prison.

36:41.600 --> 36:45.036
She's receiving care
and she's rebuilding her life.

36:45.070 --> 36:49.341
And I am
helping her do that.

36:49.375 --> 36:53.845
It's slow,
but it is happening.

36:53.879 --> 36:56.248
There's a path here, Ryan.

36:59.084 --> 37:01.720
A path to becoming whole.

37:01.753 --> 37:04.256
And I think you're brave enough
to take those first steps.

37:04.290 --> 37:05.757
And I'll walk it with you.

37:05.791 --> 37:09.861
How do I know
any of this is --

37:09.895 --> 37:12.931
If it could really all work out
for me the way you say?

37:12.964 --> 37:16.201
What you can know is what
the future will look like

37:16.234 --> 37:18.670
if you don't change it.

37:21.940 --> 37:24.242
It's going to be
like the past.

37:24.276 --> 37:26.278
No. No. I'm not --

37:26.312 --> 37:28.980
I mean, I-I can't
just leave my life!

37:29.014 --> 37:31.149
I mean, I have to put
everything in order first.

37:31.182 --> 37:32.418
I can't just walk away!

37:32.451 --> 37:34.320
Yeah, you can.

37:34.353 --> 37:36.154
You can and you have to.

37:37.356 --> 37:39.425
You deserve to.

37:41.493 --> 37:46.432
I asked you once
how someone could consent

37:46.465 --> 37:47.899
to let you in their head

37:47.933 --> 37:50.268
without knowing what
you would find there.

37:53.271 --> 37:55.374
But I knew
what you would find.

37:57.175 --> 37:59.311
Yeah, you did.

37:59.345 --> 38:01.112
But you said yes anyway.

38:03.815 --> 38:06.785
You trusted me to
bring you to this moment.

38:06.818 --> 38:14.092
**

38:14.125 --> 38:18.296
Nothing worthwhile is ever
done through thinking alone.

38:18.330 --> 38:20.532
At some point,
you have to act.

38:20.566 --> 38:27.606
**

38:27.639 --> 38:29.541
What will it look like?

38:29.575 --> 38:31.009
Where do I go?

38:31.042 --> 38:32.811
What do I do?

38:32.844 --> 38:35.881
You just walk into
a police station,

38:35.914 --> 38:37.816
any police station.

38:37.849 --> 38:40.118
-With you?
-No. I can't.

38:40.151 --> 38:43.021
They would think
I'd coerced you.

38:43.054 --> 38:44.656
They'd be thinking that
down the line somewhere,

38:44.690 --> 38:48.226
some defense lawyer's gonna
use my presence against them.

38:48.259 --> 38:50.195
But you'll come after?
When it's done?

38:52.531 --> 38:55.033
When it's done.

38:59.505 --> 39:00.839
Well then...

39:00.872 --> 39:03.308
[Breathes deeply]

39:03.341 --> 39:05.377
I guess
it's time to act.

39:08.614 --> 39:10.348
Yeah.

39:15.020 --> 39:18.056
[ Breathes shakily ]

39:20.291 --> 39:22.060
I'll see you on the path.

39:22.093 --> 39:31.169
**

39:31.202 --> 39:33.439
[ Door opens ]

39:33.472 --> 39:35.106
[ Dialing ]

39:35.140 --> 39:38.744
[ Line rings ]

39:38.777 --> 39:40.011
Hynes: Hey.

39:40.045 --> 39:41.913
I think this is it.

39:52.658 --> 39:54.760
**

39:54.793 --> 39:55.894
What is this?

39:55.927 --> 40:01.399
**

40:01.433 --> 40:03.234
Why are we here?

40:05.437 --> 40:08.139
I called your son.

40:08.173 --> 40:10.375
Said how you never stopped
keeping the faith

40:10.408 --> 40:12.744
the entire time
I've known you.

40:12.778 --> 40:14.880
Told him
what you did for them,

40:14.913 --> 40:17.449
how you'd take all
the beatings there are.

40:17.483 --> 40:19.117
How you never hated,

40:19.150 --> 40:20.852
no matter how hurt you were.

40:23.922 --> 40:24.890
D --

40:24.923 --> 40:27.158
They get it now.

40:27.192 --> 40:29.427
They're up there waiting.

40:31.362 --> 40:33.565
They want to talk.

40:33.599 --> 40:43.575
**

40:43.609 --> 40:53.519
**

40:53.552 --> 41:03.529
**

41:03.562 --> 41:11.369
**

41:11.402 --> 41:19.177
**

41:19.210 --> 41:20.846
Good call.

41:25.350 --> 41:27.519
All right.

41:29.855 --> 41:32.057
Let's just get
it over with then.

41:32.090 --> 41:33.625
Go ahead.

41:33.659 --> 41:35.426
Here's a fucked-up thing.

41:38.163 --> 41:42.200
When I needed you,
you were gone.

41:42.233 --> 41:44.970
When I told you
what was happening,

41:45.003 --> 41:47.706
you heard enough to know.

41:47.739 --> 41:50.876
I didn't get it, though.

41:50.909 --> 41:54.680
I kept thinking that you left
because you didn't understand.

41:54.713 --> 41:58.884
That if I could just be
clearer, explain better,

41:58.917 --> 42:01.286
that you'd finally step up.

42:04.556 --> 42:08.259
It took me years to see that
you just didn't give a fuck.

42:09.628 --> 42:14.566
And now, when what I really need
is for you to be gone,

42:14.600 --> 42:17.102
here you are.

42:17.135 --> 42:20.171
With your money,
your bought-off judges,

42:20.205 --> 42:22.340
your PIs hunting me down.

42:22.373 --> 42:25.577
With all the shit
that got us here...

42:25.611 --> 42:27.545
on you.

42:30.148 --> 42:32.550
So here's my offer.

42:32.584 --> 42:36.554
Never try to find
or interfere with me again.

42:36.588 --> 42:39.257
In this life or any other,

42:39.290 --> 42:42.761
by way of covering all bets.

42:42.794 --> 42:44.963
As long as you can do that,

42:44.996 --> 42:47.432
I can even thank you.

42:50.669 --> 42:53.104
You made me who I am,

42:53.138 --> 42:54.640
and I'm okay with it.

42:58.343 --> 43:00.712
How about you?

43:00.746 --> 43:03.148
Are you okay with it?

43:03.181 --> 43:09.287
**

43:09.320 --> 43:15.460
**

43:15.493 --> 43:16.895
You know what?

43:16.928 --> 43:18.930
I don't give a fuck
if you are or not.

43:18.964 --> 43:20.832
I just need to know
if we're done.

43:20.866 --> 43:22.734
For good.

43:22.768 --> 43:24.002
Last time we speak.

43:24.035 --> 43:25.837
Last time we anything.

43:25.871 --> 43:27.138
Ever.

43:29.875 --> 43:31.609
Yes.

43:34.145 --> 43:36.081
Awesome.

43:36.114 --> 43:44.856
**

44:02.974 --> 44:04.442
